Geocache Description:

27 September 2020, 14:00 - 17:00

 

Signal had himself in a bit of a pickle and needs your help!

When out geocaching, Signal followed his GPS into a room and is now locked in.  He quickly realized it wa all part of a multi-step puzzle cache.  However, he is having difficulties with the solutions to find his way out.

Join Signal at the Regina Girl Guide Center and help him escape.  You will form teams of up to 8 cachers and work together to be the "First To Free" Signal.  Afterwards there will be a time to socialize and take part in a barbeque.  Hot dogs and buns will be provided but donations of salad and dessert are welcome.

Where:  Regina Girl Guide Center - basement  1530 Broadway Ave.

Time: Sunday Sep 27 2p.m. - 5 p.m.

Please indicate how many are in your party for planning purposes.

Community Celebration Events - 2020

This Event is part of a limited release of Community Celebration Events to celebrate 20 years of geocaching. Geocachers hosted events between May 2, 2020 and December 31, 2020. Learn more about Community Celebration Events on the Geocaching Blog.
